{"event": "ACTIVE_TASK_UPDATED", "task_id": "ORCH-7402458F", "goal": "I want to rebuild YahyaTel. Ask me the most important questions before planning.", "active_agent": "manager", "rate_status": "SAFE", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T18:40:11.370330+00:00"}
{"event": "ACTIVE_TASK_UPDATED", "task_id": "ORCH-D8199351", "goal": "Project context: YahyaTel is an imaginary Oman-based telecom/ecommerce FYP platform inspired by Omantel. It serves B2C consumers with ISP services and B2B businesses with predictive analytics. The B2B side predicts customer churn using XGBoost and suggests retention strategies. I will provide the model and fine-tuning data. We will use FastAPI for the backend, chatbot support, English-Arabic translation, and database communication. Version 1 exists and should be reused after downloading it from the web. Timeline is 2 weeks. No real budget. This is a demo, not a real telecom operator. Success means a working system. Ask only the most important missing questions before creating the rebuild plan.", "active_agent": "manager", "rate_status": "SAFE", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T18:50:38.923485+00:00"}
{"event": "ACTIVE_TASK_UPDATED", "task_id": "ORCH-12A09B26", "goal": "YahyaTel = imaginary Oman telecom/ecommerce FYP platform\n\nB2C:\n- ISP service platform for consumers\n\nB2B:\n- churn prediction dashboard\n- XGBoost model\n- retention strategy suggestions\n- chatbot\n- English ↔ Arabic translation\n- database communication through FastAPI\n\nConstraint:\n- 2 weeks\n- working demo matters more than perfect production\n- version 1 exists and should be reused\nFor retention strategies, do not keep only hardcoded messages. Better approach:\n\nXGBoost predicts churn risk\n↓\nSystem identifies top risk factors\n↓\nRule-based retention engine suggests strategy\n↓\nOptional chatbot explains strategy in Arabic/English\nExample retention engine:\n\nHigh monthly charges → offer discount / custom plan\nLow usage → suggest cheaper plan\nFrequent complaints → priority support callback\nContract ending soon → renewal offer\nSlow internet complaints → technical check / router upgrade\nBusiness customer → account manager follow-up", "active_agent": "manager", "rate_status": "SAFE", "timestamp": "2026-05-15T18:52:01.432454+00:00"}
